transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling, this is John, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hello, this is John, how can I help you?

Speaker 1: This message has been transcribed.

Speaker 2: One moment while I notify...

Speaker 1: Hello?

Speaker 2: Hi, this is John, how can I help you?

Speaker 1: Yeah, um, the pills that I got are not working.

Speaker 2: Okay, can I get your name and zip code so I can look at your account, sir?

Speaker 1: Lloyd Green, my what?

Speaker 2: Zip code.

Speaker 1: Oh, 98032?

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: 64th Avenue in Kent?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Okay, so, um, they don't work at all or it's just not as strong as you want it to be?

Speaker 2: Because it could be you just need 100 milligrams.

Speaker 1: Yeah, well, yeah, they might not be strong enough.

Speaker 2: Okay, well, as a courtesy to you, do you want me to send you out a test of 10 hundred milligrams just to try and see if those work better for you?

Speaker 1: Yeah, please.

Speaker 2: Okay, so this will be a one-time thing where I'm sending you free pills, but I'm going to allow you to try the 100 milligrams and then let us know how it goes.

Speaker 1: Okay, thank you.

Speaker 2: Welcome, sir, have a good one.

Speaker 1: You too, bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
